On December 22, 2017, the President signed two bills into law. The first bill, H.R. 1370, provides appropriations for the fiscal year 2018 and extends certain authorizations for the Foreign Intelligence Surveillance Act until January 19, 2018. It also includes emergency funding for missile defense and ship repair in the Department of Defense, extends public health programs and funding for the Children's Health Insurance Program, and appropriates funding to the Veterans Choice Fund. The bill also includes a direction regarding the budgetary effects of certain Acts. The second bill, H.R. 1, provides comprehensive tax reform for individuals and businesses, and repeals the individual mandate under the Affordable Care Act.